description:
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare Science Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Neurophysiology Practitioner Full time qualified to at least ANS Part I (EEG) standard and RCCP registered. &lt;/strong&gt;This is a permanent appointment at AfC band 5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to join a highly motivated, enthusiastic team with a busy and varied workload performing EEGs on patients of all ages both in the department and at the bedside on wards/ICU/NICU, Ambulatory EEGs with and without video, Nerve conduction studies, Evoked Potentials and Visual Electrophysiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to work independently to perform and factually report EEGs on a variety of patients both in the department and at the bedside in the wards/ICU. Ability to perform evoked potentials and/or nerve conduction studies independently would be expected although training will be given if these skills are not in place. Encouragement and support will be given to acquire additional skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Nikki Broomfield on 01752 437986 ornicola.broomfield@nhs.net to discuss&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
